---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const authors = [
	{ name: 'Shengmin Liu', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Yash Mathur', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Tyler Brady', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Malavikha Sudarshan', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Yasin Sonmez', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
	{ name: 'Murat Arcak', affiliation: 'University of California, Berkeley' },
];

const projectLinks = [
	{ label: 'Paper', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Code', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Poster', href: '#' },
	{ label: 'Demo Video', href: '#' },
];

const highlights = [
	'Integrates the SHARC processor and control simulator with CARLA driving environments.',
	'Models perception, planning, and control latency instead of assuming instantaneous computation.',
	'Sets up safety-critical experiments where small delays measurably change driving outcomes.',
];

const scenarios = [
	{
		title: 'Unprotected Left Turn',
		description:
			'Measure how planning delay changes gap acceptance, braking timing, and near-collision behavior in busy intersections.',
	},
	{
		title: 'Emergency Cut-In',
		description:
			'Study whether delayed perception and planning cause unsafe following responses when a neighboring car abruptly merges.',
	},
	{
		title: 'Crosswalk Occlusion',
		description:
			'Test how hardware-aware latency affects pedestrian reaction time when detections are partially obstructed and time critical.',
	},
];

const roadmap = [
	'Connect SHARC timing outputs to CARLA perception-planning-control execution loops.',
	'Build repeatable driving scenarios with tunable processor and task-graph parameters.',
	'Quantify how computational delays shift metrics such as collision rate, comfort, and policy stability.',
];

const bibtex = String.raw`@misc{sharcdrive2026,
  title        = {SHARC-Drive: Hardware-Aware Driving Simulation with SHARC and CARLA},
  author       = {Your Capstone Team},
  year         = {2026},
  note         = {Project page boilerplate}
}`;
---

<Layout
	title="SHARC-Drive | SHARC CARLA"
	description="SHARC-Drive integrates SHARC with CARLA to study how processor-level computation latency affects autonomous driving performance."
>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10 sm:px-8">
		<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-950 sm:text-5xl">
				SHARC-Drive
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-700">
				Hardware-aware driving simulation with SHARC and CARLA
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-6 gap-y-3 text-[15px] text-zinc-700">
				{
					authors.map((author) => (
						<p>
							<span class="font-medium text-zinc-900">{author.name}</span>
							<span class="text-zinc-500"> · {author.affiliation}</span>
						</p>
					))
				}
			</div>
			<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
				{
					projectLinks.map((link) => (
						<a
							class="rounded-md border border-zinc-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-zinc-800 transition hover:bg-zinc-50"
							href={link.href}
						>
							{link.label}
						</a>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-4xl">
			<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<div class="flex aspect-[16/9] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
					Teaser image, system diagram, or short demo video
				</div>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-3 text-center text-sm text-zinc-600">
				Replace this placeholder with the main SHARC-CARLA figure or a short demonstration clip.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="overview" class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Abstract</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Modern autonomous driving systems depend on real-time execution of perception, planning, and control algorithms on integrated onboard computing systems. Open-source simulators such as CARLA capture vehicle and environment dynamics in high fidelity, but typically abstract away how long it takes to process data. SHARC-Drive extends SHARC and integrates it with CARLA to create a hardware-aware simulation framework for systematically studying how computational delays affect autonomous decisions in scenarios where even small timing shifts can cause unsafe actions.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Overview</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				The main goal is to move beyond idealized driving simulation and evaluate autonomous policies under realistic compute constraints. Instead of assuming that perception, planning, and control complete instantly, SHARC-Drive makes execution delay part of the simulation.
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				{
					highlights.map((highlight) => (
						<li>{highlight}</li>
					))
				}
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Method Overview</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<div class="flex aspect-[16/9] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
					System architecture figure placeholder
				</div>
			</div>
			<ol class="mt-5 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				{
					roadmap.map((item) => (
						<li>{item}</li>
					))
				}
			</ol>
		</section>

		<section id="scenarios" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Qualitative Comparisons</h2>
			<p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				Use this section for side-by-side scenario rollouts, similar to the reference project pages.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
				{
					scenarios.map((scenario) => (
						<div>
							<div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
								<div class="flex aspect-[4/3] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
									Media placeholder
								</div>
							</div>
							<h3 class="mt-3 text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-950">{scenario.title}</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-700">{scenario.description}</p>
						</div>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</section>

		<section id="results" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">Performance Results</h2>
			<div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50">
				<div class="flex aspect-[16/9] items-center justify-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
					Performance plot or results figure placeholder
				</div>
			</div>
			<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-8 text-zinc-700">
				<li>Collision rate under varying processor and scheduling configurations</li>
				<li>Reaction-time shift between nominal and latency-aware simulations</li>
				<li>Control smoothness and braking aggressiveness under delay</li>
				<li>Scenario-level analysis of unsafe delayed actions</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section id="details" class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl pb-8">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-950">BibTeX</h2>
			<pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50 p-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-700"><code>{bibtex}</code></pre>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
